.Im MicroEmacs variable|macrodevelop
.so me.tni
.TH $mouse-x 5
.XI $mouse-x - "Mouse X (horizontal) position"
.XI $mouse-y - "Mouse Y (vertical) position"
.SH NAME
.Me "|$mouse-x"
$mouse-x \- Mouse X (horizontal) position
.br
.Me "|$mouse-y"
$mouse-y \- Mouse Y (vertical) position
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB$mouse-x\fR \fIinteger\fR
.sp
0 <= \fIinteger\fR <= 
.Hl "$screen-width" $screen-width  5
\- 1
.sp
\fB$mouse-y\fR \fIinteger\fR
.sp
0 <= \fIinteger\fR <= 
.Hl "$screen-depth" $screen-depth  5
\- 1
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B $mouse-x
and 
.B $mouse-y
are  automatically  set to the  position of the mouse at the last mouse event,
where an event is a button press or release.  Initialized to 0,0. The top left
character of the screen is coordinate 0,0 bottom right is
.Hl $screen-width $screen-width 5 ,
.Hl $screen-depth $screen-depth 5 .
.SH NOTES
These  variables  can not be set. Any  attempt  to set them will  result in an
error.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht set-cursor-to-mouse 2 ,
.Ht $mouse-pos 5 ,
.Ht $cursor-x 5 ,
.Ht $screen-depth 5 ,
.Ht $screen-width 5 .
.ad
.FH
